<servinfosub id = "AENAP70B5104018003">
<title>
Troubleshooting
</title>
<attention1>
<list1 type = "unordered">
<item>
<ptxt>
Perform road test in a place where there is no traffic to prevent an accident.
</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>
Road test should be performed with two persons, a driver and a tester, on a level road.
</ptxt>
</item>
</list1>
</attention1>
<diag type = "test" id = "AENAP70B5104018004">
<testgroup id = "AENAP70B5104018005">
<question>
Was “A/T Control System Check” performed?
</question>
<result type = "yes"/>
<action>
<ptxt>
Go to Step 2.
</ptxt>
</action>
<result type = "no"/>
<action>
<ptxt>
Go to 
<intxref refid = "AENAP70B5104001">A/T Control System Check</intxref>
.
</ptxt>
</action>
</testgroup>
<testgroup id = "AENAP70B5104018006">
<title>
DTC check
</title>
<question>
Is DTC P0711, P0712, P0713, P0717, P0722, P0961, P0962, P0963, U0073 and/or U0100 detected?
</question>
<result type = "yes"/>
<action>
<ptxt>
Go to applicable DTC troubleshooting.
</ptxt>
</action>
<result type = "no"/>
<action>
<ptxt>
Go to Step 3.
</ptxt>
</action>
</testgroup>
<testgroup id = "AENAP70B5104018007">
<title>
Shift solenoid valve “A” / “B” circuit check
</title>
<test1>
<ptxt>
Perform running test under the following conditions and measure voltage between “shift solenoid “A” drive circuit” at TCM connector and ground; and “shift solenoid “B” drive circuit” at TCM connector and ground.
</ptxt>
<list1 type = "unordered">
<item>
<ptxt>
Engine coolant temperature is in normal operating temperature.
</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>
Select lever is in “D” range.
</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>
Drive vehicle with 4th gear condition referring to “Automatic Gear Shift Table” under 
<intxref refid = "AENAP70B5104010">Road Test</intxref>
.
</ptxt>
<spec>
<title>
Voltage between TCM connector and ground
</title>
<ptxt>
“Shift solenoid “A” drive circuit” at TCM connector and ground: 0 – 0.3 V
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
“Shift solenoid “B” drive circuit” at TCM connector and ground: 9.5 – 16 V
</ptxt>
</spec>
</item>
</list1>
</test1>
<question>
Are results as specified?
</question>
<result type = "yes"/>
<action>
<ptxt>
Faulty shift solenoid valve, circuit or A/T.
</ptxt>
</action>
<result type = "no"/>
<action>
<ptxt>
Go to Step 4.
</ptxt>
</action>
</testgroup>
<testgroup id = "AENAP70B5104018008">
<title>
O/D off switch signal check
</title>
<test1>
<ptxt>
With ignition “ON”, check voltage between O/D off switch circuit at TCM connector and ground.
</ptxt>
<spec>
<title>
O/D off switch signal specification
</title>
<ptxt>
O/D off switch pressed: 0 – 0.3 V
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
O/D off switch released: 8.4 – 16 V
</ptxt>
</spec>
</test1>
<question>
Are results as specified?
</question>
<result type = "yes"/>
<action>
<ptxt>
Substitute a known-good TCM and recheck.
</ptxt>
</action>
<result type = "no"/>
<action>
<paragroup>
<ptxt>
Faulty O/D off switch or its circuit.
</ptxt>
</paragroup>
</action>
</testgroup>
